item.title: Good rsc server
item.dc:creator: @RSCShadow RSCShadow
item.description:
@RSCShadow wrote:

It really depends what you want to play. RSCE almost never has any noticeable updates (updates that the players can actually use, and not just back-end stuff none of the players will ever notice). A lot of other newer servers do have more updates, along with a faster EXP rate.

item.title: Good rsc server
item.dc:creator: @Intoxication Intoxication
item.description:
@Intoxication wrote:

[quote=“Kryptix, post:2, topic:373952”]Yep there’s a leak somewhere but it’s only a issue when there’s lots of players online for the whole period, for example back when we had a smaller playerbase it was restarted almost weekly. It’s difficult to compare to any other server because they have such a smaller playerbase. Even if they have 30 online compared to our 200 (for example) you can guarantee that they far less people logging in and out than we do which is where the problem is I think. Don’t get me wrong we’ve looked into it on numerous occasions and the reason why Zilent disappeared is because he hates not being able to fix something, the leak was in RSCD and is also in RSCA as well, it’s very difficult to test because any minor change that could resolve it won’t actually be seen until the game engine tick starts spiking after the garbage collector runs continuously after the memory reaches ~700mB.

Regardless of that it’s still the most stable server, even if the network drops for some reason the game server happily runs in the background so it takes next to no maintenance except the restarts.[/quote]

I can think of 3 things that people neglected to look into (and I mean seriously not even touched), 2 of which could very well be your problem.
Regardless, after a year+ of countless hours searching through your source, you should have pretty much fixed the leak, or at the very least identified the problem by now.

What type of tests have you preformed to conclude that it’s logging in/out, or tests for anything for that matter?
